{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Lower VED caps: \u00a310 for Zero Emission + \u00a330 for Internal Combustion vehicles",
        "additional_details": "As Zero Emission Vehicle (ZEV) owners, we understand the need to contribute something toward maintaining the transport infrastructure, however we believe that as this has previously been an emissions-based VED, the owner of a ZEVs should pay the current lowest VED rate of \u00a310 per year, irrespective of the age of the vehicle.\r\nWe want this to become the \"new\" zero emissions charge, with Internal Combustion Engine (ICE) VED tariffs starting from \u00a330 per year.\r\n",
        "background": "As of 1st April 2025, all private Zero Emission Vehicles (ZEVs) will be charged \u00a310, \u00a320 or \u00a3195 a year for Vehicle Excise Duty (VED). We feel that as ZEVs do not produce emissions, they should not be required to pay a higher VED tariff. ",
